description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Apprenticeship Opportunity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Contract Type: &lt;/strong&gt;Fixed Term 18 Months&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary Range: &lt;/strong&gt;£9,903 - £17,105 per annum pro rata&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Learning Partner Team within Corporate Nursing, Midwifery and Allied Health Professions are looking for an enthusiastic and motivated individual to join their team and provide a comprehensive, effective and professional administrative support to the Learning Partners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will provide an initial contact service to the Learning Partner Team, directing initial queries, supporting with the administration and collation of data and information and have excellent Microsoft Word and Excel skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will support the learning &amp; funding administration coordinator and learning partners with administration of training information in relation to Continuous Professional Development (CPD), Continuous Workforce Development (CWD) requests and collation and administration of the Trust wide Training matrix and Training Needs analysis (TNA).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will also provide assistance and cross cover to the wider teams within Learning and Education where appropriate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Alongside the above you will have excellent communication and organisational skills, the ability to multi-task, work under pressure, thrive on being part of a team, whilst producing work that is reliable and accurate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for someone who will be proactive, and have the confidence to deal with anything with enthusiasm.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an apprentice you will be trained in the full range of our office procedures. You will enjoy using a computer, meeting with and helping others and have a desire to provide a high standard of customer service. You must be able to prioritise your own work to meet deadlines, have the ability to follow instructions and have excellent communication skills, both verbal and written. You will be confident, have a mature and flexible approach, be a good time keeper and have the ability to work unsupervised to ensure the effective coordination of duties.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return we will ensure that you receive all the training you need to be able to do this role fully and competently. You will be released for study and supported to achieve a Customer Service Practitioner Level 2 Apprenticeship Standard. You will receive 27 days annual leave and be entitled to a range of discounts on services and products from a number of retailers and organisations in the local area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mininum Entry Criteria:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;GCSE Grade 9-4/A-C in English and Maths, Level 2 Functional Skills in Maths and english (or equivalent qualificaitons)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Applicants are not eligible to apply for this apprenticeship if they have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A Customer Service qualification or apprenticeship (in the same field) at level 2 or level 3&lt;/strong&gt; (If applicants have other qualifications similar to customer service, an eligibility check will need to be completed to ensure they are eligible to do this apprenticeship)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please read the Job Description and Person Specification attached, and ensure that your statement in support of your application reflects these criteria.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information on this post or an informal discussion, please contact: theanna.desancho@nhs.net, Nursing &amp; Midwifery Learning Partner&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note that this vacancy will close once we have received a sufficient number of applications.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
